-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 DETAB
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Format:

     detab filename

Purpose:

The DETAB command takes the text in the specified file and removes the TABs 
within it (to reverse the action, use the ENTAB command).

Example:

Remove the spaces from the file named detab.c and write it to the file named 
detab.new.

     detab detab.c > detab.new
